It is essential to keep the look and feel of a digital product in the way intended. For that purpose a design rules must be documented in a place where you will find it when creating markup and visual components.

Here is a comprehensive, self-describing template for documenting Design System decisions for a website. This template is structured to ensure clarity, consistency, and completeness, and can be used as a living document for your team.

> **How to Use This Template:**
>
> - Fill in each section with your project’s specific decisions and rationale.
> - Update as the design system evolves.
> - Use tables and diagrams where helpful.
> - Reference real code, tokens, or design files when possible.


